Classes must be prefixed with the type of the module: .c-my-component – it's a component and should be stored in 01_components . .m-my-module – it's a module and should be stored in 02_modules . .o-my-organism – it's an organism and should be stored in 03_organisms . .t-my-template – it's a layout and should be stored in 04_templates . .u-my-utility – it's aa utility and should be stored in utils/_utils.scss . BEM When using BEM avoid nesting of elements and modifiers. WRONG: .my-block {
  &__element {

  }
} RIGHT: .my-block {

}

.my-block__element {

} This helps a lot while debugging and improves the readability of the code. Constants Module and component based constant must be prefixed with the module name, i. e. $breadcrumbs-background . Global constants must be prefixed with $global- .

Almost all dimensions and metrics be based on a basline value of 8px . This value is defined in utils/_constants.scss as $global-baseline as a unitless value. To use the baseline in your CSS code please use the u-baseline mixin: .element {
  @include u-baseline(5, margin-bottom);
} The first param defines the factor (in this case: 5 * 8 = 40px). The second param defines the property. You can add any CSS property you want.

The grid system relies heavily on Foundation with only minimal configuration,
specifically with regard to breakpoints, margins, and gutters. Check out Foundation's documentation on XY grid to learn more about
the underlying system. The max width of the grid is 1200px with a total of 12 columns. Column and
gutter (space between columns) width scales with the viewport. However, on
large displays each column is 60px wide. The grid uses padding to separate
columns. The flex grid is globally activated. Usage in HTML The usage in the HTML should be avoid, but it's possible of course.
Due the fact that Foundation forgot the option to nest grids in flex mode,
there's a custom helper for nested rows: <div class="row u-row--nested"/> .u-row--nested will remove the unwanted paddings. Usage in CSS: .module {
  @include xy-grid-container;
  @include xy-grid;
}

.module__column {
  @include xy-cell(6);
} @include xy-grid-container; @include xy-grid; will add the Foundation grid row.
